inline defines an inline function. It should look like the following: inline foo(x: int, y: int): int { print("foo"); add-int(x, y)
} inline is the same as define except that the definition is always expanded at compile-time. For example, if you write define use-inline-foo(): int { let val = foo(10, 20) in val
} The compiler will translate the above code into the following: define use-inline-foo(): int { let val = let tmp1 = 10 in let tmp2 = 20 in print("foo"); add-int(tmp1, tmp2) in val
}

