| c2
} In this case, the type of c1 is some-adt, and the type of c2 is other-adt(?M), where the ?M must be inferred by the compiler. If a constructor c isn't nullary, the type of c is the function type that takes specified arguments and turns them into the ADT type. For example, consider the following code: data some-adt {
| c1(foo: int)
} data other-adt(a: type) {
| c2(bar: bool, buz: other-adt(a))
} In this case, the type of c1 is (foo: int) -> some-adt, and the type of c2 is <a: type>(bar: bool, buz: other-adt(a)) -> other-adt(a).

