A term of type meta a can be created using the syntactic construct box. The syntax of box is as follows: // here is layer (n+1)
// - x1: &a1 at (n+1)
// - ...
// - xm: &am at (n+1)
box x1, ..., xm { // here is layer n // - x1: a1 at n // - ... // - xm: am at n e1
} Given a term e: A, the type of box x1, ..., xn {e} is meta A. Note that the types of xis must be of the form &A. box turns &a1, ..., &an into a1, ..., an inside its body.

